---
/**
 * Why Lumecon — three positions reflecting the framing: replacing
 * both the consultant and the overpriced legacy software, the
 * high-frequency data canon + beyond, and AI for small / messy
 * regions.
 *
 * Each position is a <details> element so the section reads as a
 * progressive-disclosure rail: the headline + animated icon are
 * always visible, and a click expands the longer body. Cuts the
 * visible word count on the homepage by roughly half while keeping
 * the depth for visitors who want it.
 */
import '../styles/why.css';
---
<section class="why" id="how" aria-labelledby="why-title">
  <div class="why-inner">
    <header class="why-header">
      <p class="why-header__kicker reveal-soft">Why Lumecon?</p>
      <h2 class="why-header__title reveal-soft hl-block hl-block--gold" id="why-title" data-stagger="1">Built with you, not for you.</h2>
      <!-- Accent box wraps the lede paragraphs so the prose reads
           as one purposeful block. White card on the cream section
           with a teal rail down the left edge. -->
      <div class="why-header__lede-box reveal-soft" data-stagger="2">
        <p class="why-header__lede">Lumecon sits between expensive software and expensive consulting: the scale of one, the judgment of the other, the bad incentives of neither.</p>
        <p class="why-header__lede">The incumbent workflow keeps impact analysis as a once-a-year luxury, designed before the internet, costing ten times as much <em>per study</em>, arriving months late. Lumecon makes it part of how your team works.</p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="why-grid">
      <details class="why-stat">
        <summary class="why-stat__head">
          <span class="why-stat__icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" class="why-icon why-icon--replace">
              <!-- Consultant invoice (left, taller) -->
              <rect x="3" y="3.5" width="7.5" height="14" rx=".4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linejoin="miter"/>
              <line x1="4.7" y1="6.4" x2="8.8" y2="6.4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width=".85"/>
              <line x1="4.7" y1="8.6" x2="8.8" y2="8.6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width=".85"/>
              <line x1="4.7" y1="10.8" x2="7.6" y2="10.8" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width=".85"/>
              <line x1="4.7" y1="14.5" x2="8.8" y2="14.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1"/>
              <!-- Software box (right, with little chrome dots) -->
              <rect x="12.5" y="7" width="8.5" height="11" rx=".4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linejoin="miter"/>
              <line x1="12.5" y1="9.7" x2="21" y2="9.7" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width=".9"/>
              <circle cx="13.7" cy="8.4" r=".4" fill="currentColor"/>
              <circle cx="15" cy="8.4" r=".4" fill="currentColor"/>
              <rect x="14" y="11.5" width="5.5" height="4.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width=".85"/>
              <!-- Gold strike sweeping bottom-left → top-right -->
              <line class="why-icon-replace__strike" x1="2" y1="21" x2="22" y2="3" stroke="#0FB5A5" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="butt"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
          <p class="why-stat__k"><strong>Lumecon replaces</strong> the software <em class="why-stat__amp">and</em> the consulting team behind it.</p>
          <span class="why-stat__chev" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </summary>
        <div class="why-stat__body">
          <p class="why-stat__v">The existing platforms charge per geography, per user, per data tier. The consultants who actually run them charge by the billable hour, often with junior analysts doing the work. Lumecon collapses both into one flat annual subscription: unlimited studies, every geography, every team member. Our incentive is to keep you, not to nickel-and-dime each study.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="why-stat">
        <summary class="why-stat__head">
          <span class="why-stat__icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" class="why-icon why-icon--unlock">
              <!-- Folder back (tab) -->
              <path d="M3 7 L9 7 L11 5 L21 5 L21 9.5 L3 9.5 Z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linejoin="miter"/>
              <!-- Folder front (slightly tilted at the top for the open hinge) -->
              <g class="why-icon-unlock__lid">
                <path d="M3 9.5 L21 9.5 L21 20 L3 20 Z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linejoin="miter" fill="var(--white, #fff)"/>
                <!-- Data rows inside -->
                <line x1="6" y1="13" x2="16" y2="13" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width=".9"/>
                <line x1="6" y1="15.6" x2="14" y2="15.6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width=".9"/>
                <line x1="6" y1="18.2" x2="17" y2="18.2" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width=".9"/>
              </g>
              <!-- Gold spark rising from inside the folder -->
              <g class="why-icon-unlock__spark">
                <path d="M18.5 6.4 L18.5 1.6 M16.1 4 L20.9 4 M16.8 2.3 L20.2 5.7 M20.2 2.3 L16.8 5.7" stroke="#0FB5A5" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linecap="butt"/>
              </g>
            </svg>
          </span>
          <p class="why-stat__k"><strong>Lumecon delivers</strong> consulting-quality output without the consulting incentives.</p>
          <span class="why-stat__chev" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </summary>
        <div class="why-stat__body">
          <p class="why-stat__v">Consulting engagements bill by the hour, so the work expands to fill the hours: junior analysts hand-clean data, the senior partner you actually want to talk to shows up at meetings, and you pay top rates for both. Lumecon's outputs match the rigor (public sources serious models rely on like ACS, BEA, LODES, QCEW; direct, indirect, induced, and total impact verified against the existing platforms; every assumption surfaced; the audit trail attached) without the billable-hour drag. Input-output models are forty years old; the data, assumptions, and workflow shouldn't be.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="why-stat">
        <summary class="why-stat__head">
          <span class="why-stat__icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" class="why-icon why-icon--region">
              <!-- Outer rough region -->
              <path class="why-icon-region__outline" d="M5 7.5 L8.5 3.5 L15 4.8 L19.5 8 L18.8 14.4 L14 19 L7.3 17.5 L4 13.2 Z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linejoin="miter" pathLength="100" stroke-dasharray="100" stroke-dashoffset="100"/>
              <!-- Inner sub-boundary (sub-region) -->
              <path class="why-icon-region__inner" d="M9 10 L13.5 9 L14.5 13 L11 14.5 Z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" stroke-linejoin="miter" pathLength="100" stroke-dasharray="100" stroke-dashoffset="100"/>
              <!-- Gold "light" pulse inside -->
              <circle class="why-icon-region__pulse" cx="11.7" cy="11.6" r="2.4" fill="#0FB5A5" opacity="0.18"/>
              <circle class="why-icon-region__dot" cx="11.7" cy="11.6" r="1.2" fill="#0FB5A5"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
          <p class="why-stat__k"><strong>Lumecon is</strong> built around Cedar, not bolted on after.</p>
          <span class="why-stat__chev" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </summary>
        <div class="why-stat__body">
          <p class="why-stat__v">Cedar isn't a chatbot tacked onto a legacy stack. Lumecon was built around it from day one. Cedar reads source files, structures messy inputs, surfaces every assumption, and reshapes the same study for the council memo, grant narrative, board deck, or public release you need next. Each study stays in your workspace, but the analytical engine improves with use: better multipliers, new data signals, refined methodology compound across customers. Existing software siloes every engagement; Lumecon learns.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
